BT /F2 15 Tf 54 662 Td (Submission Recommendation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628 Td (Do not submit immediately if you still have an hour. The implementation is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 615 Td (submit-ready, but the extra time is valuable for packaging the design story:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602 Td (workflow, tradeoffs, tests, failure modes, and why the evaluation numbers are) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 589 Td (not being overclaimed.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568 Td (Practical recommendation: use 40-45 minutes to polish and rehearse, then submit) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 555 Td (with a 10-15 minute buffer. Do not wait until the final minute.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534 Td (The key framing: "The system scores very well on the supplied eight-file demo) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 521 Td (suite, but I do not claim 100% real-world accuracy. I treat that as a regression) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508 Td (signal and describe what I would add for production validation.") Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 477 Td (1. One-Minute Opening Pitch) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 443 Td (I built a case-agnostic RAG system for detectives investigating cybercrime case) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 430 Td (files. It ingests any set of text case files, embeds them into a vector) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 417 Td (database, lets a detective ask a natural-language question, retrieves the most) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 404 Td (relevant evidence with confidence scores and relevance reasons, then generates) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 391 Td (a grounded investigation report with source citations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 370 Td (The design uses multi-step retrieval instead of a single nearest-neighbor) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 357 Td (lookup because investigations often require evidence chaining across multiple) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 344 Td (documents, and the corpus includes deliberate red herrings.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 313 Td (2. End-to-End Workflow) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 279 Td (1. Case files are placed in data/ as .txt files.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 264 Td (2. app/ingest.py loads every non-empty text file.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 249 Td (3. Each document is embedded using text-embedding-3-small.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 234 Td (4. Embeddings, document text, and metadata are stored in ChromaDB with cosine) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 219 Td (   distance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 206 Td (5. A detective asks a question through the UI or POST /api/investigate.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 191 Td (6. The system expands the detective query into focused sub-queries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 176 Td (7. The original query and expanded sub-queries are embedded in a batch.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 161 Td (8. ChromaDB returns top-k candidate documents per query.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 146 Td (9. The system merges duplicates and keeps the best cosine similarity as the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 131 Td (   document confidence score.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 118 Td (10. An LLM relevance grader reranks and filters candidates against the original) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 103 Td (    detective question.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 90 Td (11. The report generator uses only the retrieved evidence to produce a Markdown) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 75 Td (    investigation report with citations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 526 28 Td (Page 1) Tj ET
endstream
