BT /F2 15 Tf 54 740 Td (4. Database Choice: ChromaDB) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 706 Td (Chosen database: ChromaDB persistent vector store with cosine search.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 685 Td (Why it fits this project:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 672 Td (- Simple local setup for a take-home/demo.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 657 Td (- Supports persistent collections.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642 Td (- Stores embeddings, documents, and metadata together.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 627 Td (- Supports cosine distance, which maps naturally to confidence as) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 612 Td (  1 - cosine distance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 599 Td (- Low operational overhead compared with running a separate vector database.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576 Td (What to say if asked about production scale:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 563 Td ("For this project, ChromaDB is the right choice because the corpus is small and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550 Td (the goal is demonstrability. In production, if we needed multi-user access,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 537 Td (authorization, audit logs, horizontal scaling, or cloud operations, I would) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524 Td (consider pgvector, Pinecone, Weaviate, or a managed vector store depending on) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 511 Td (the surrounding infrastructure.") Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 480 Td (5. Retrieval Strategy and Justification) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 446 Td (Chosen strategy: Multi-step retrieval.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 425 Td (Pipeline:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 412 Td (1. Expand the user query into 3-4 focused sub-queries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 397 Td (2. Search vector DB with original query and expanded sub-queries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 382 Td (3. Merge and deduplicate results.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 367 Td (4. Compute confidence as max cosine similarity across matched queries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 352 Td (5. Use an LLM relevance grader against the original question.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 337 Td (6. Return ranked evidence and separately show excluded documents with reasons.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 314 Td (Why not single-step:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 301 Td (- Single nearest-neighbor retrieval can only return one document.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 286 Td (- Some detective questions require multiple documents, such as access method) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271 Td (  plus laundering path.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 258 Td (- The corpus intentionally includes misleading files with overlapping terms.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 243 Td (- Embedding similarity alone can rank red herrings highly when vocabulary) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 228 Td (  overlaps.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 207 Td (Empirical justification from the project:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 194 Td (- Single-step top-1: 81% recall overall, 50% recall on multi-document queries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 179 Td (- Naive top-k threshold: 94% recall but only 31% precision.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 164 Td (- Full multi-step pipeline: 100% recall on the small demo suite and 75%) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 149 Td (  precision, while preserving all multi-document answers.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 128 Td (How to phrase the 100% number:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 115 Td ("The 100% is only on the supplied eight-query labeled fixture. I do not claim) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 102 Td (that as real-world accuracy. It tells me the design passes the assignment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 89 Td (scenario and has no known regression on that fixture.") Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 526 28 Td (Page 3) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
