BT /F2 15 Tf 54 740 Td (6. Ranking and Confidence) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 706 Td (Confidence score:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 693 Td (- ChromaDB returns cosine distance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 678 Td (- The system converts it to similarity: confidence = 1 - distance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 663 Td (- If a document is retrieved by multiple sub-queries, it keeps the best score.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648 Td (- The UI shows confidence bars and the top matched query for each document.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 625 Td (Why this is useful:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 612 Td (- Detectives see not only the final answer, but which files were retrieved and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 597 Td (  why.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584 Td (- Excluded documents are visible too, reducing the black-box feel.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 561 Td (Limit:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 548 Td (- Similarity score is not probability.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 533 Td (- It should be explained as retrieval confidence, not truth confidence.) Tj ET
